description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Staff nurses Band 5 Registered Nurse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are professional and passionate and think going the extra mile for your patients is the norm then you are what we are looking for. We are looking for a motivated &lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; to join our professional and friendly team in Enfield&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enfield Health provides community health services for the borough of Enfield within the larger Barnet Enfield and Haringey Mental Health NHS Trust, which provides integrated mental health services for young people and adults in Barnet, Enfield and Haringey. We serve a population of 1.2 million and operate services from five main inpatient sites and a further 25 sites in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint &lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurses&lt;/strong&gt; in District Nursing Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will take responsibility for the effective assessment, planning and delivery of skilled nursing care to patients in their own homes or other settings as appropriate under the direction of the caseload manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although the post holder has access to advice he/she is expected to work largely unsupervised. In addition, the post-holder is expected to supervise junior staff, Assistant Practitioner and Health Care Assistants including student nurses on placement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nihinlola Akinyemi (Lola) Area Manager District Nursing, (West Locality)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: lola.akinyemi@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 020 8702 4545&lt;/p&gt;
